ary colleges. Geography Unbound presents an insightful portrait of a crucial period in the development of modern geography, whose unstable disciplinary status is still very much an issue today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aGeographyxPhilosophyxHistoryy18th century. 0aGeographyxPhilosophyxHistoryy19th century. 0aGeographyzFrancexHistoryy18th century. 0aGeographyzFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aGeography. 70(DE-601)1043942850(DE-588)4020216-1aGeografie2gnd 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  ageography, france, science, exploration, discovery, mapmaking, cartography, letronne, von humboldt, volney, cassini iv, military college, jesuit, encyclopedie, history, philosophy, academia, higher education, nonfiction, description, mapping, maps, earth sciences, regionalism, travel, engineers, egypt, expedition, archaeology, cabinet, cosmography.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1990-1999z978311066785140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226300535423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226300535/original  a978-3-11-066785-1  University of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1990-1999c1990d1999  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles